said.The parolee appeared before the Waterval Magistrate's Court
on the 6 December for murder and attempted murder charges and his cases were
postponed to 29 January for bail application.Netsiongani had a domestic dispute with his 25-year-old wife
and subsequently stabbed her several times with a sharp object and further
stabbed their two children aged five and 3-years-old several times throughout
their bodies before fleeing the scene. Netsiongani was a parolee after he was sentenced to 15 years
